## Interviewer Reflection

**Most important thing learned:**
There is a *role* in every group — the asker — that is doing the work of compensating for platform fragmentation. We had been thinking of the problem as individual. It is actually distributed across groups, with one person typically absorbing the cost.

**What to do differently next time:**
Ask whether the interviewee is the asker or the non-asker in their group early. It would have given me the framing for the entire conversation up front instead of at the end.

